article.description: Henderson, Bowling Green beat Chicago State, 58-35
article.headline: Henderson, Bowling Green beat Chicago State, 58-35
article.linkText: Henderson, Bowling Green beat Chicago State, 58-35
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ohio -- Anthony Henderson scored 14 points and Jehvon Clarke added 11 to lead Bowling Green to a 58-35 win over Chicago State on Saturday. Richaun Holmes had nine points, five rebounds and four blocked shots and Jovan Austin had seven assists for Bowling Green (8-3), which held Chicago State to its lowest scoring output since a 57-35 loss to Southern Utah on Feb. 16, 2002. Holmes now has 500 career rebounds. Anthony Glover's layup about a minute into the game gave Chicago State (4-13) a 2-0 lead before a 3-pointer by Henderson sparked -- and back-to-back 3's by Denny capped -- a 17-2 Bowling Green run. The Cougars, who made just 6 of 25 (24 percent) field goals in the first half, trailed by at least 12 the rest of the way. A three-point play by Delvin Dickerson with 10:36 remaining gave the Falcons a 31-point lead, 54-23, their biggest of the game.
